Changelog Modelio 3.7.1

Released on March the 8th 2018

Fixes / Improvements:

    New ‘Show numbers’ graphic option for Sequence Messages.
    It is now possible to delete elements from the semantic model explorer.
    Fixed issues with Sequence diagrams.
    Fixed issues in BPMN Diagrams.
    Fixed issues with BPMN migration.
    Fixed issues with BPMN Import/Export.
    Fixed issues with Provided/Required Interfaces.
    Fixed issues with Audit preferences.
    Fixed issue with orthogonal links drawing.
    Fixed issue with state transitions labels in model explorer.
    Fixed issue with associations multiplicity display in diagrams.
    Fixed issues with the XMI import/export.

Notes:

The Rich Note feature has been validated under the following platforms:

    Windows 8.1 and Windows 10 using the following ‘offices’:
        MS Office 2010
        MS Office 2013
        MS Office 2016
        LibreOffice 5.3.6
        LibreOffice 5.4.2

    Ubuntu 14.04 & 16.04 and CentOS 6 & 7 using the following ‘offices’:
        LibreOffice 4.2.8
        LibreOffice 5.1.2
        LibreOffice 5.3.6
        LibreOffice 5.4.2
